    "discriminators": [
     "The purest tone in the taxonomy: essentially a sinusoid. partial_count of 1-2, spectral_flatness near zero, harmonicity near 1, and almost no distortion. Nothing else in UCS is this clean.",
     "It is also the most pitch-MOBILE. A human glides: a wolf whistle is literally a sweep up and then back down, so expect a large pitch_slope magnitude and a big spectral_centroid_deviation_hz on an otherwise perfect tone.",
     "WHISTLES-MECHANICAL sits higher (2-4 kHz), starts harder as pressure snaps the resonator into oscillation, and holds its pitch; a pea whistle also warbles fast, which a human cannot do.",
     "Any horn is far lower with far more partials. Stylized whistles go to CARTOON-WHISTLE."
    ],
